  <datafield tag="245" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Three-body calculation of elastic and inelastic scattering of deuterons on 24 Mg</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="260" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="c">2016-03</subfield>
    <subfield code="t">published</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="300" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">9</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Deuteron–nucleus scattering is described using exact three-particle equations. The theory is formulated in an extended Hilbert space allowing the excitation of the target nucleus. Alt, Grassberger, and Sandhas equations for transition operators are solved in the momentum-space framework including the Coulomb interaction via the screening and renormalization method. The calculations are performed for elastic and inelastic scattering of deuterons on 24 Mg using the rotational model for the excitation potential. A reasonable agreement with the experimental data for the first excited state <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msup><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>+</mo></mrow></msup></math> of 24 Mg is achieved when the quadrupole deformation parameter <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msub><mrow><mi>β</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0.47</mn></math> is used. This new value is more consistent with the inelastic proton scattering data requiring <math altimg="si3.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msub><mrow><mi>β</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>≈</mo><mn>0.5</mn></math> than previous determinations <math altimg="si4.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msub><mrow><mi>β</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>≈</mo><mn>0.4</mn></math> based on two-body deuteron–nucleus models.</subfield>
    <subfield code="9">Elsevier</subfield>
  </datafield>
